<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-637-332  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 637 332.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  July 9 1990 n598 p75(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Poll: where you'd like to work. (electronics and computerengineers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rostky, George.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Readers of 'Electronic Engineering Times' were asked what kind ofcompany they would like to work for.andP;  Hewlett-Packard was citedthe most times.andP;  Good companies were defined as having goodmanagement, being successful in their markets, having strongtechnology, and being fair to employees.andP;  Bad companies werecharacterized by frequent layoffs, insensitivity to employeeneeds, short-term orientation, discriminatory practices, lack oforganization, high turnover, and few opportunities foradvancement.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     SurveyEmployeeJob SatisfactionElectronic IndustryWork EnvironmentPersonnel Problems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>